description: Highly Versatile and beautiful Adirondack Guideboat 15 with Piantedoso Ro-Wing. Custom hand built in Maine by East West Custom Boats. 298 cm Sculling Oars. Current Ohio Registration. Hand Laid Hull with cloth and roving in isothalic resin. Varnished Mahogany Gunnels and nose pieces. Positive seal scupper hole with lock out. Hull weight only 70lb with positive sealed flotation in the bow and stern compartments. Length: 15 ft 9 inches. Beam 37" at shear, 18" at waterline. Draft 4". Two rowing trim positions, 2 cane passenger seats. Sliding seat has quick removable padding over wood. Retail is $5430 new, ordered in advance, excluding freight. Excellent for cross training, the Guideboat 15 will row all day at 5 mph easy, 6 to 7 mph with moderate exertion, and 8 to 10 mph at race pace by seasoned scullers. This Guideboat design has covered the 65 mile round trip Lake George to Ticonderoga distance in record time consistently over the last six years, making the 65 mi run in less than 12 hours, without the sliding seat unit! As to versatility, the Guideboat 15 can carry a multitude of gear and people very efficiently in calm or rough water conditions. Unlike racing shells the Guideboat 15 will row right through motorboat wakes, wind chop and small surf. This hull is among the driest of all rowboats. the Guideboat 15 has one of the two fastest traditional Guideboat hull designs while also retaining a high degree of stability in the water. It is an excellent training boat, fishing boat, family boat or cruising boat because of it's stability. As is the case with all Guideboats the more weight that is carried the more stable they become due to their superior designed "V" shaped hull. It tracks beautifully without a fin and only draws a few inches of water with people and gear aboard.
title: Adirondack Guideboat 15, Custom Built, Ro-Wing, Sculling Oars

description: Up for sale is a 1967 Aquasport 22-2 Flatback. Completely restored and documented in 2007/2008 from the stringers up with all composite materials by Bateau2.  https://boatbuildercentral.wordpress.com/2015/10/29/an-in-depth-rebuild-of-a-classic-aquasport-22-flatback/ During the restoration the stringers were replaced with solid core material, the transom was enclosed and a porta bracket was added. It was rigged with a 2007 Mercury 150 Optimax which currently has 360 hours and was recently serviced with a new oil pump installed and given a clean bill of health. I cruise at 4000 rpm at 30mph. The boat was just repainted Seafoam Green in December 2015. Also new within the last 6 months is the trolling motor (motor guide XI5), the Simrad GO7 chart plotter/fishfinder with navionics . I recently re-plumbed the live well adding a 1600 gph pump and new 1 1/8 flex hose. The front casting platform has three hatches, the middle hatch has a cast net bucket inside to keep your net out of the way while fishing. There is so much more to this boat but talking about it does not do it justice. A lot of money has gone into this classic boat and to restore one like this would cost a lot more than the asking price. I am including the aluminum trailer which is perfectly fit for the boat and pulls great. Please feel free to email or text any questions, phone calls are difficult to answer during the day but text and email I can reply quickly. If necessary I can call you in the evenings. The boat is titled and I do have the clean title in hand. Update: I have been flooded with questions on the boat so I decided to list out some of the other items on the boat. Engine: 2007 Mercury Optimax (2 stroke) 150hp. Hours: 360 Hydraulic steering Morse controls Porta Bracket adjustable height lift. Comes with a 3 blade aluminum prop and a 4 blade SS prop. Dual 8ft. power poles Hydraulic trim tabs, needs new relays. . .boat really does not need tabs but I left them on without installing new relays. Ping pong style scullpers. The hull was professionally painted 01/16 sea foam green. Motor Guide Xi5, bought in 03/2016. 24v system. 2 dedicated batteries for the trolling motor attached to a battery tender trickle charger. New Simrad Go7 chartplotter, sonar, downscan w/ navionics +. New Kenwood head unit, JVC amp, 12 inch sub, and 2 new Pioneer speakers. New Rule 1600 GPH live well pump and new 1 1/2" inlet line. 2 bank on board battery charger 2 batteries under the console for motor and house on a battery selector. Freshwater wash down pump and tank w/ hose under console. Marine radio under console LED front and rear deck lights 6 rod holders along the railing, 4 rod holders in seat/livewell 2 Seat post pads installed in front deck, included is a small wedge seat and an umbrella which was made to fit through the posts. The boat has 2 bilge pumps front and rear, both operate correctly. Large Bimini top Trailer: Dual axle Fastload aluminum rail trailer. 4 bunks custom fit for the boat. New front rollers, new strap, new chain, new guide posts and new lights.
title: Restored 1967 Aquasport 22-2 flatback
